text: The Cato Trough or Chesterfield Trough is an oceanic trough in the Coral Sea of the South Pacific Ocean. It separates the continental crust of Australia and Zealandia to within and has a depth of . The trough is underlain by oceanic crust, having formed as a result of seafloor spreading from about 63 to 50 million years ago. ==References== ==External links== *Marine Gazetteer Placedetails Category:Coral Sea Category:Oceanic trenches of the Pacific Ocean
